{
  "text": "Thourani and colleagues [CITATION_1] retrospectively analyzed 572 patients who underwent bioprosthetic MVR over a 5-year period with regards to treatment with either 4 -6 weeks of postoperative warfarin or no warfarin. They reported that although the use of postoperative warfarin did not reduce the incidence of stroke at early follow-up, it was associated with a trend for improved long-term outcomes.",
